The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Online Reporter Matabeleland North province Minister for Provincial Affairs and Devolution Richard Moyo is commissioning a classroom block at the Joanne Fuyana Primary school in Nyamandlovu. <img class="wp-image-677536 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/WhatsApp-Image-2023-01-31-at-2.03.00-PM.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/WhatsApp-Image-2023-01-31-at-2.03.00-PM.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/01/WhatsApp-Image-2023-01-31-at-2.03.00-PM-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Minister Richard Moyo touring the classroom block at Joanna Fuyana Primary School The classroom block was constructed in partnership between Government and the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints. Senior Government officials, church members, teachers, pupils and parents at the school are also in attendance.